column5: Hey fellas and ladies. Just signed on to the site here and thought I would say hello to everyone. I hope I can get assitance for what I may need and I will be more than happy to share some of my tips and secrets with all of you. Anyways have a good day all. ATF
welcome aboard so what do you fish for.....  for many of us right now..not much fishing, boats are put away and waiting for ice to get thick

Welcome to the boards!  These guys can definitely give you great advice, as I've been poking around myself picking up a wealth of information, and it appears I'll be following your posts as well!  I think I've gathered enough intel to kick my boss's ass next year when we head to the great lakes for salmon fishing.  Of course... there never is enough information for me, so all your tips are very well appreciated!

I fish for pretty much everything. In the last year I have gotten right into steelhead and salmon fishing. In my first year I have caught 2 chinook 1 coho 1 brown and too many steelhead to count. The thing I like about fishin the tribs is you don't need a boat so you don't have to worry if its put away.
Welcome ATF. When it comes to info, opinions, reports,hard luck,good luck,great and bad luck you'll find it all here. As one trib fisher to another...looking forward to your reports.
Welcome to  the OFC!!  Great place to spend time  blyght
welcome aboard cant wait to see some reports. cheers and great fishing
You've come to the right place!! This board has provided my wife and I hours and hours of entertainment and knowledge since we joined!
Welcome Aboard!!  You'll love it here.  Joey
Welcome to a great family on the internet.  Look forward to your posts.
I doubt you're the only one "Addicted to Fishin" around here.   You shall fit in just fine.  Welcome aboard.
